com.telekom.m2m.cot.restsdk.smartrest

Class SmartResponseTemplate

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telekom.m2m.cot.restsdk.smartrest.SmartTemplate
      • com.telekom.m2m.cot.restsdk.smartrest.SmartResponseTemplate

  • public class SmartResponseTemplate
extends SmartTemplate
    A SmartResponseTemplate is used server side to transform a REST response into one line of a SmartREST response.

    All templates for the given X-Id are matched against the response. Each template, if it does match, can extract data from the JSON, turning it into a CSV line.

    See SmartRestApiIT for examples.

      • SmartResponseTemplate

        public SmartResponseTemplate(String msgId,
                             String base,
                             String condition,
                             String[] pattern)
        Construct a new SmartResponseTemplate from individual parameters. Parameters should be raw, unescaped.
        Parameters:
        msgId - the unique (for one X-Id) message-ID of this template
        base - the JSONPath base that this template assumes
        condition - the JSONPath that needs to match for this template to be evaluated by the server
        pattern - the JSONPaths from which information is to be extracted
